verbose_text: The Ab-tps1, Ab-tps2 and Ab-tre dsRNA had no obvious effect on the transcript level of Ab-Actin (Ab-28sRNA as an internal control, using primers Ab-28sRNA-F and Ab-28sRNA-R); however, whichever TPS gene was silenced would make the transcript of the other TPS gene reduce and the silencing of Ab-tre would make the transcripts of both TPS genes reduce, but the transcript level of Ab-tre would also be reduced by Ab-tps1+ Ab-tps2 silencing (XREF_FIG A).
